<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Ending With -MENT — Scrabble Suffix Scoring Guide</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The -MENT suffix turns verbs into nouns (judge→judgment, equip→equipment) and carries 7 base points thanks to the M tile's 3-point value. With over 400 valid -MENT words in SOWPODS, this suffix consistently produces bingo-length words from everyday verb roots that are easy to spot and hard to challenge.</p>

<p>Learning -MENT patterns helps you convert common 4-5 letter verbs into high-scoring 8-9 letter plays that earn the coveted 50-point bingo bonus.</p>

<p>The suffix is also defensive gold — knowing which verbs accept -MENT helps you block extension spots before your opponent can exploit them.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why -MENT Matters in Scrabble</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">M(3)+E(1)+N(1)+T(1) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">400+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -MENT words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5–14</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter length range</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>The M tile contributes 3 points — more than E, N, or T — making -MENT slightly more valuable than -TION as a suffix. Combined with the natural bingo length of most -MENT words, this suffix is a reliable scoring engine.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring -MENT Words</h2>

