<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Extend verbs on the board:</span> If MOVE, TREAT, or AGREE is already played, adding -MENT creates a high-scoring extension. Look for verbs near the board edge that can accept the suffix without running out of space.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">M tile management:</span> M is worth 3 points and you only get 2 in the bag. If you have E, N, T alongside M, you have -MENT ready. Save it for a bingo rather than wasting M in a short word like MAT or MOP.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Standalone -MENT words:</span> CEMENT, MOMENT, FOMENT, and LAMENT are all valid 6-letter plays that don't require a verb root. They fit tight boards and score well thanks to the M tile. Keep these in your mental toolkit.</p>
  </div>
</div>

